	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can see wild price swings on items.  Last night I bought this baby for my new high elf enchanter alt for 15pp.  The seller had sent out a note, &quot;All my stuff goes!&quot; and so I sent him a tell offering 15pp for the CCS.  He went for it.<br><br>I have taken to keeping a spreadsheet of the items I'm looking for, and each time I visit the Bazaar I just do a search and go down the list to see what the current prices are.  I also keep a &quot;historic low&quot; price for each item so that I have some sense of what the range can be.<br><br>Bottom line is if you have patience, you can usually over the course of a few sessions find something for a decent price.<br><br>Hope this helps,<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Feb 28 13:56:28 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Macairn<br>Shaman<br>19th Season<br>E'ci Server</td></tr>
